Investigate the performance of the Linux Scheduler

By Garrett Long

---Executables---
./benchmarks - A program which reports benchmarks for three Linux scheduling schemes
./pi - A simple program for statistically calculating pi
./mix - A simple i/o and CPU bound program.
./rw - A simple i/o program.

---Examples---
Build:
 make

Clean:
 make clean

pi:
 ./pi
 ./pi <Number of Iterations>


rw:
 ./rw
 ./rw <#Bytes to Write to Output File>
 ./rw <#Bytes to Write to Output File> <Block Size>
 ./rw <#Bytes to Write to Output File> <Block Size> <Input Filename>
 ./rw <#Bytes to Write to Output File> <Block Size> <Input Filename> <Output Filename>

mix:
 ./mix

benchmarks:
 sudo ./bencmarks

